WEBVTT

00:21.479 --> 00:24.482
<i>One of the most important
decisions you'll ever make</i>

00:24.482 --> 00:26.192
<i>is who to spend your life with.</i>

00:28.486 --> 00:29.654
<i>Who they are.</i>

00:31.448 --> 00:33.491
<i>Who you are when you're with them.</i>

00:35.702 --> 00:38.997
<i>And if that's the person
you really wanna be.</i>

00:38.997 --> 00:42.417
<i>♪ Pain in my chest, pain in my breast
Yeah, you were the key ♪</i>

00:42.417 --> 00:44.335
<i>♪ And you know ♪</i>

00:44.335 --> 00:46.588
<i>♪ You know I hate to fight ♪</i>

00:46.588 --> 00:51.092
<i>♪ You know, you know I can't believe... ♪</i>

00:51.092 --> 00:52.510
Now fuck me.

00:56.055 --> 00:59.184
<i>Fairy tales absolutely do come true.</i>

01:01.936 --> 01:05.482
<i>But sometimes you have to
go through hell first to get there.</i>

01:06.274 --> 01:08.068
Hold on. Wait.

01:08.068 --> 01:09.819
- Oh, come on.
- Don't! Just--

01:10.528 --> 01:11.613
Just don't.

01:16.785 --> 01:20.121
I came to you six months ago with a ring,

01:20.121 --> 01:22.207
with a dream of a life,

01:22.207 --> 01:23.625
and you said no.

01:23.625 --> 01:25.585
- I know.
- No, you don't.

01:27.670 --> 01:30.673
It took everything I have to get over you.

01:32.091 --> 01:33.092
I had to--

01:34.010 --> 01:36.221
I had to bury all those feelings...

01:37.305 --> 01:38.723
just to stay alive.

01:40.892 --> 01:41.935
And now...

01:45.188 --> 01:46.231
it's too late.

01:51.903 --> 01:53.279
I met someone.

01:54.072 --> 01:55.073
Gigi.

01:55.073 --> 01:55.990
She's...

01:57.826 --> 01:59.452
- She's a model.

02:00.620 --> 02:02.122
Of course she is.

02:02.122 --> 02:03.414
And she's pregnant.

02:05.959 --> 02:07.877
We're gonna start a family together.

02:09.129 --> 02:09.963
I can...

02:11.047 --> 02:13.758
finally make things right.

02:15.844 --> 02:17.971
Be the man you always wanted me to be.

02:20.306 --> 02:21.891
Just with someone else.

02:21.891 --> 02:22.809
Hey.

02:22.809 --> 02:24.310
Oh, my God.

02:25.687 --> 02:27.438
This is so embarrassing. Wow.

02:28.523 --> 02:30.024
I never should've come. Um--

02:30.024 --> 02:33.444
I just-- I've been trying
to forget about you and this...

02:34.654 --> 02:37.824
part of me for months now, you know?

02:37.824 --> 02:42.162
And then I saw you
at Sasha's book event and I--

02:42.162 --> 02:43.621
What event?

02:44.330 --> 02:46.249
This afternoon, at the pavilion.

02:46.249 --> 02:48.877
No, I wasn't there, Billie.

02:49.377 --> 02:50.962
Yes, you were.

02:50.962 --> 02:52.130
I saw you.

02:56.718 --> 02:58.052
Oh, my God.

03:01.139 --> 03:02.348
What about Cooper?

03:03.391 --> 03:04.392
Huh?

03:05.143 --> 03:06.644
What was your plan?

03:06.644 --> 03:08.688
Were you just gonna hide this from him?

03:09.272 --> 03:10.189
I don't know.

03:13.484 --> 03:14.485
I guess so.

03:14.485 --> 03:16.279
That's not who you are.

03:17.405 --> 03:18.698
Or who you wanna be.

03:22.410 --> 03:23.953
Forget me, all right?

03:26.456 --> 03:27.373
Forget us.

03:29.500 --> 03:31.169
You have a choice you need to make.

03:31.169 --> 03:33.379
No, I should just go home

03:33.379 --> 03:37.133
and, like, pretend
like none of this ever happened.

03:37.133 --> 03:38.176
Or not.

03:40.887 --> 03:42.931
You are fearless, Billie Mann.

03:44.599 --> 03:46.309
You need to remember that.

03:48.895 --> 03:51.940
And decide what you really want
out of your life.

03:53.274 --> 03:54.108
<i>Billie?</i>

03:55.151 --> 03:56.152
<i>Billie?</i>

03:58.112 --> 03:59.030
Billie?

04:01.783 --> 04:03.076
Come on, girl.

04:05.203 --> 04:07.247
- Hey, hey, hey.
- You're back!

04:07.247 --> 04:08.373
Of course!

04:08.373 --> 04:10.500
- And I'm exhausted.
- Oh.

04:11.459 --> 04:13.920
But I brought reinforcements.

04:13.920 --> 04:14.879
Yeah.

04:16.047 --> 04:17.840
And you got a couch.

04:18.800 --> 04:20.885
I finally unpacked all those boxes,

04:20.885 --> 04:23.513
which means this is really happening.

04:24.681 --> 04:26.099
This is my life now.

04:26.099 --> 04:29.435
For the three days a week
you're not in Connecticut with your kids.

04:29.435 --> 04:30.812
- Thanks.
- Hey.

04:31.312 --> 04:34.023
Some time to yourself
is one of the perks of divorce.

04:34.023 --> 04:37.735
Or so says the DILF
I shacked up with in San Fran.

04:38.319 --> 04:40.071
You gotta do a book tour.

04:40.071 --> 04:43.574
A paramour in every city doesn't suck.

04:44.158 --> 04:45.868
I need to write a book first.

04:45.868 --> 04:48.579
Well, now you have time.

04:49.330 --> 04:51.708
Look, we need to get you
out of this apartment

04:51.708 --> 04:53.751
and back in the game.

04:53.751 --> 04:55.795
Mm? Mm?

04:55.795 --> 04:56.713
- Okay.

04:57.755 --> 04:58.589
Oh, my God.

04:58.589 --> 05:00.258
Get your ass in here.

05:03.261 --> 05:05.221
These clothes are crusty, girl.

05:05.221 --> 05:07.098
Haven't really been going out.

05:07.098 --> 05:08.599
No shit.

05:08.599 --> 05:10.184
It's been months.

05:10.184 --> 05:12.603
You need to stop punishing yourself.

05:12.603 --> 05:14.188
Put on some real clothes.

05:14.188 --> 05:15.898
Maybe a little lip gloss.

05:15.898 --> 05:18.067
Come find our new neighborhood joint.

05:18.067 --> 05:19.485
I don't know, Sash.

05:19.485 --> 05:20.945
Well, I do.

05:20.945 --> 05:23.197
Plus, I got news.

05:23.197 --> 05:25.450
Guess whose bestselling best friend

05:25.450 --> 05:29.787
is going to be interviewed
live on national TV tomorrow

05:29.787 --> 05:32.248
by mother-loving Soledad O'Brien?

05:32.248 --> 05:33.791
- No.
- Yes!

05:34.500 --> 05:35.376
What?

05:40.048 --> 05:41.591
Cheers, honey.

05:42.633 --> 05:43.843
Yes.

05:48.556 --> 05:51.017
No. What is that? Your phantom diamond?

05:51.017 --> 05:54.562
You miss the noose-like golden handcuff
that thing had become?

05:54.562 --> 05:56.064
It's just weird.

05:56.064 --> 05:58.191
It's not weird.

05:58.191 --> 06:00.526
It's just like old times.

06:00.526 --> 06:03.446
We are the hottest women in this place

06:03.446 --> 06:06.741
and plenty of dudes
are rightfully checking us out.

06:06.741 --> 06:09.285
- Like him.
-  Oh.

06:09.285 --> 06:10.745
-  And him.
-  Stop it.

06:10.745 --> 06:14.040
- And him, and him, and him.
- Enough. Put your-- Stop!

06:14.040 --> 06:15.833
I will not.

06:15.833 --> 06:19.462
Because you have nothing
to feel guilty about.

06:20.129 --> 06:21.798
Oh. Well, in that case,

06:21.798 --> 06:23.800
let me just go get my fuck on right now.

06:23.800 --> 06:24.926
- Whoa!
- Oh!

06:24.926 --> 06:26.052
- Oh, my--
- Easy, killer.

06:26.052 --> 06:27.637
I'm so sorry.

06:27.637 --> 06:29.764
Oh, my God. Here. No, I got it.

06:29.764 --> 06:31.808
Ow!

06:31.808 --> 06:33.017
Oh, my God.

06:33.017 --> 06:34.310
Are you okay?

06:34.310 --> 06:36.813
Perfect, yeah.
I was ready for a new nose anyway.

06:36.813 --> 06:38.689
Do you think it's broken?

06:40.775 --> 06:41.943
I don't know.

06:41.943 --> 06:43.569
Maybe you could check it out?

06:43.569 --> 06:44.570
What do you think?

06:45.154 --> 06:46.906
I think you're gonna be fine.

06:47.490 --> 06:50.868
Maybe I could get
your insurance information just in case?

06:50.868 --> 06:54.831
I got a pretty high deductible.
Might be better to just self-pay.

06:55.540 --> 06:59.752
Anyway, have a great night.
I'm really sorry about that.

06:59.752 --> 07:01.129
Whoa, whoa. What's your name?

07:03.214 --> 07:05.133
I never come this far uptown,

07:05.133 --> 07:09.512
but my buddy's playing around the corner
at The Beacon so we stopped in.

07:09.512 --> 07:11.389
Now I think I know why.

07:12.306 --> 07:13.683
Oh, my God. Why?

07:13.683 --> 07:15.101
Because it's kismet?

07:15.101 --> 07:17.520
Let me buy you a drink. Find out.

07:17.520 --> 07:19.397
Okay. Well...

07:19.397 --> 07:22.275
I already have a drink so--

07:22.275 --> 07:23.776
Actually...

07:25.862 --> 07:28.114
Hmm. Problem solved.

07:29.240 --> 07:31.033
Her name's Billie, by the way.

07:32.243 --> 07:34.745
Nice to meet you, Billie.

07:35.413 --> 07:37.165
Nice to meet you...

07:37.748 --> 07:38.833
Majid.

07:39.417 --> 07:41.210
- Majid.
- It's Persian.

07:42.044 --> 07:42.920
And you?

07:43.713 --> 07:44.589
Uh, yeah. Yeah.

07:44.589 --> 07:45.506
Half.

07:45.506 --> 07:46.424
My dad.

07:48.551 --> 07:50.845
Listen, I'm flattered.

07:50.845 --> 07:53.931
Though clearly not a big believer in fate.

07:54.515 --> 07:56.434
I'm just out
having a drink with my friend.

07:56.434 --> 07:58.060
I'm not really--

07:58.060 --> 07:59.187
Available?

07:59.979 --> 08:02.482
I figured you were too hot to be single.

08:04.150 --> 08:06.235
So who's the lucky guy?

08:12.950 --> 08:13.784
You're back.

08:16.996 --> 08:18.414
You're still awake.

08:21.626 --> 08:22.460
Good.

08:24.128 --> 08:25.213
We need to talk.

08:25.880 --> 08:30.301
I know I said that everything was fine...

08:31.594 --> 08:34.764
and I was hoping it would be fine,
but the truth is...

08:37.725 --> 08:38.976
it's not.

08:40.061 --> 08:42.897
Is this your way of explaining
where you've been all night?

08:44.649 --> 08:45.816
I went to see Brad.

08:45.816 --> 08:47.318
Yeah, no shit.

08:52.114 --> 08:54.242
Put a tracker on your phone, Billie.

08:56.410 --> 08:57.662
You did what?

08:59.413 --> 09:01.082
I knew you'd go back to him.

09:01.082 --> 09:02.959
This isn't about Brad.

09:02.959 --> 09:04.210
This is about me.

09:04.210 --> 09:06.462
It's about us. It's about our marriage.

09:06.462 --> 09:08.839
Which is pretty much over,
don't you think?

09:08.839 --> 09:10.591
I think we need to find out.

09:10.591 --> 09:11.634
Oh, please.

09:11.634 --> 09:15.054
I should have left you six months ago
and I was about to,

09:15.054 --> 09:17.306
but your fucking boyfriend
convinced me to stay,

09:17.306 --> 09:20.643
telling me that I was the one you wanted,
which is clearly not true.

09:20.643 --> 09:23.354
I wanted it to be true.

09:23.354 --> 09:26.315
But the only reason it's been working
at all the last six months

09:26.315 --> 09:30.820
is because I took the blame for everything
right up until what happened with Trina.

09:30.820 --> 09:33.197
Cooper, I wanna be honest...

09:33.781 --> 09:37.159
with myself and you
about who I am and what I want.

09:37.159 --> 09:39.954
And I want us to be able
to talk through it.

09:39.954 --> 09:41.914
We should go to counseling.

09:41.914 --> 09:43.374
Fuck counseling.

09:43.374 --> 09:44.834
And fuck you.

09:45.418 --> 09:46.836
Okay. Cooper.

09:46.836 --> 09:50.214
Cooper, you don't mean that, okay?
I know you're upset--

09:50.214 --> 09:51.382
I'm not.

09:51.382 --> 09:52.300
I--

09:53.718 --> 09:55.094
I'm just done.

10:03.644 --> 10:05.771
There's no guy.

10:05.771 --> 10:06.814
Lucky or otherwise.

10:06.814 --> 10:08.691
Then lucky me.

10:08.691 --> 10:09.609
No.

10:12.570 --> 10:13.821
Okay, you know what?

10:15.740 --> 10:16.699
Screw it.

10:18.075 --> 10:21.078
You don't wanna go out with me, okay?

10:21.078 --> 10:24.290
I am a messy mess right now

10:24.290 --> 10:25.708
who just blew up her life.

10:25.708 --> 10:27.460
I mean, kind of unintentionally,

10:27.460 --> 10:30.921
but if I'm really being honest,
completely intentionally.

10:30.921 --> 10:33.758
I have two young kids.
I'm in the middle of a bitter divorce.

10:33.758 --> 10:34.800
But even worse,

10:34.800 --> 10:38.095
I'm pining away for the love of my life,
who is with somebody else now,

10:38.095 --> 10:39.722
a fucking model,

10:39.722 --> 10:41.015
and they're having a baby,

10:41.015 --> 10:43.893
so I'm supposed to figure out
how to move on without him,

10:43.893 --> 10:48.356
but the only problem is
I'm pretty sure I never, ever will.

10:50.191 --> 10:51.692
You're something else.

10:52.276 --> 10:53.778
- So I've been told.
- No.

10:54.403 --> 10:55.446
I like it.

10:56.030 --> 10:57.823
Usually, you have to put in three dates

10:57.823 --> 11:00.701
before you get to
what's really going on with someone.

11:01.702 --> 11:03.829
Is that the new three date rule?

11:03.829 --> 11:05.539
At this point in my life...

11:05.539 --> 11:08.000
it feels so much better
to just skip the dance.

11:08.000 --> 11:09.460
Cut to the chase.

11:09.460 --> 11:12.171
Not that I don't like to dance.

11:12.171 --> 11:16.133
I'm very much looking forward
to doing the dance with you, Billie.

11:16.133 --> 11:17.093
Okay.

11:17.093 --> 11:18.761
You're insane. You realize that?

11:18.761 --> 11:23.140
Well, not everything
has to make sense to make sense.

11:24.225 --> 11:27.353
Besides, the time
right after you blow up your life...

11:28.521 --> 11:30.398
it's usually the most exciting.

11:30.398 --> 11:31.399
Trust me.

11:32.608 --> 11:34.151
What does that mean?

11:34.151 --> 11:35.486
Just that...

11:36.487 --> 11:39.073
what seems like it was
the worst day of your life...

11:39.740 --> 11:41.826
might actually have been the best.

11:43.411 --> 11:44.245
Okay.

11:45.413 --> 11:48.707
Thank you,
but I am a PhD candidate in psychology

11:48.707 --> 11:53.337
which means I am drowning in aphorisms
about how crises build resilience.

11:53.337 --> 11:56.966
Uh, "The future lies in you."
"Make your own tomorrow."

11:56.966 --> 11:58.884
I mean, it's all I think about.

11:58.884 --> 12:00.302
Maybe that's your problem.

12:00.886 --> 12:02.263
Too much thinking.

12:04.056 --> 12:05.516
Give me your phone.

12:05.516 --> 12:07.101
Excuse me?

12:07.101 --> 12:09.353
It's how the kids do it these days.

12:10.604 --> 12:11.605
Tomorrow night.

12:12.982 --> 12:13.899
Eight o'clock.

12:13.899 --> 12:16.193
I know a great place in the Village.

12:16.193 --> 12:17.570
Let me take you out.

12:18.195 --> 12:19.738
Get your mind on something else.

12:19.738 --> 12:21.157
Okay?

12:21.157 --> 12:22.074
Dude.

12:23.159 --> 12:24.326
We're good to go.

12:25.911 --> 12:26.745
Kismet.

12:27.788 --> 12:28.622
Yeah.

12:34.503 --> 12:38.674
Now that's what I'm talking about! Ow!

12:38.674 --> 12:40.801
I'm going out!

12:41.427 --> 12:43.762
Let's go, baby!

12:47.892 --> 12:48.767
Daddy?

12:49.435 --> 12:50.853
What's up, bud?

12:50.853 --> 12:52.771
Olga needs you downstairs.

12:52.771 --> 12:54.732
All right. I'm coming.

13:06.160 --> 13:06.994
You all right?

13:06.994 --> 13:09.622
How long is Olga gonna be staying with us?

13:11.707 --> 13:12.875
For a while.

13:14.543 --> 13:18.589
- She's really helping, don't you think?
- I want Mommy to come home.

13:19.882 --> 13:21.300
She'll be here tomorrow.

13:22.885 --> 13:24.887
We're taking turns now, remember?

13:24.887 --> 13:28.307
I want us to be home together
like a family.

13:33.521 --> 13:34.813
I know you do, bud.

13:38.984 --> 13:40.653
Hey, Olga. What's going on?

13:40.653 --> 13:41.737
This.

13:43.322 --> 13:44.323
Ellary!

13:44.323 --> 13:46.242
Oh, my God. Come here, baby.

13:46.242 --> 13:48.744
Come to Daddy, Els. Come to Daddy.

13:48.744 --> 13:51.372
Come here. Look at you go! Aw!

13:51.372 --> 13:52.623
Come here.

13:53.249 --> 13:55.751
Come here! Aw!

13:57.419 --> 13:59.588
Oh! You did so good!

13:59.588 --> 14:00.839
Look at you.

14:00.839 --> 14:02.716
I'll send Billie the video.

14:07.263 --> 14:08.097
Great.

14:10.099 --> 14:12.434
<i>Look, marriage isn't for everyone.</i>

14:12.434 --> 14:15.145
What's important
is that we question everything.

14:15.145 --> 14:19.358
Test our assumptions and the institutions
which have grown from them.

14:19.358 --> 14:22.611
Hmm. Would you ever
consider marriage yourself?

14:22.611 --> 14:23.862
Hmm...

14:23.862 --> 14:26.866
I recently received a proposal actually,

14:26.866 --> 14:28.325
but turned it down.

14:28.325 --> 14:30.744
Marriage just isn't
the right paradigm for me.

14:31.328 --> 14:34.540
So your book
is not exactly a how-to guide.

14:34.540 --> 14:36.208
Far from it.

14:36.208 --> 14:39.169
My idea of having it all
means doing what I want, when I want,

14:39.169 --> 14:41.046
with whomever I want.

14:41.046 --> 14:43.841
Hmm. An independent woman.

14:43.841 --> 14:44.884
For life.

14:44.884 --> 14:45.926
Sasha Snow.

14:45.926 --> 14:47.303
<i>The Third Way.</i>

14:47.303 --> 14:50.139
Get it, read it, live it.

14:50.139 --> 14:53.726
This is the new world order, ladies,
and I like it.

14:54.476 --> 14:55.686
We'll be right back.

14:55.686 --> 14:58.439
<i>And we're out.
Back in three with the weather.</i>

14:58.439 --> 15:00.566
- What a pleasure.
- I'm such a huge fan.

15:00.566 --> 15:01.734
Thank you.

15:06.196 --> 15:08.532
It was better
than I ever could've imagined.

15:08.532 --> 15:09.450
Right?

15:10.075 --> 15:12.745
- I am completely out of my body right now.

15:13.621 --> 15:15.331
My God, Sash.

15:38.479 --> 15:40.856
<i>♪ The very thought ♪</i>

15:41.899 --> 15:43.776
<i>♪ To make me come... ♪</i>

15:45.653 --> 15:48.530
<i>♪ Over to yours ♪</i>

15:48.530 --> 15:50.783
<i>♪ It weighs upon my head ♪</i>

15:50.783 --> 15:54.453
<i>♪ And I feel the charge ♪</i>

15:55.287 --> 15:56.789
<i>♪ Pull me south... ♪</i>

15:56.789 --> 15:58.040
I love you.

15:58.749 --> 16:00.459
I love you so, so much.

16:04.421 --> 16:07.383
You did it.
Everything we talked about in college,

16:07.383 --> 16:09.426
everything we dreamt about.

16:09.426 --> 16:10.761
Times about a thousand.

16:10.761 --> 16:13.806
And you look stunning.

16:15.015 --> 16:17.851
- Oh. Oh, shit.
- No, I got it.

16:18.936 --> 16:19.979
Hey, Billie.

16:19.979 --> 16:21.689
Hi, Kam.

16:26.235 --> 16:28.737
Oh. Hey. Here.

16:29.905 --> 16:32.241
You carry a handkerchief.

16:32.241 --> 16:33.450
Seriously?

16:33.450 --> 16:35.744
Something I picked up in the outback.

16:35.744 --> 16:38.247
Never know when
you're gonna need a tourniquet.

16:38.747 --> 16:40.624
What are you doing here?

16:41.125 --> 16:43.544
I am getting interviewed too.

16:43.544 --> 16:46.380
Raising awareness for
our disaster relief efforts in the Congo.

16:46.380 --> 16:47.881
You're kidding.

16:47.881 --> 16:50.300
No, I left the Cleveland Clinic.

16:50.300 --> 16:53.721
Now I run
an international medical non-profit.

16:54.805 --> 16:56.890
I guess my bleeding heart
got the better of me.

16:58.142 --> 16:59.935
I didn't know you were in Cleveland.

16:59.935 --> 17:03.230
Well, what's it been? 17 years?

17:04.314 --> 17:07.109
Hey, let me take you to dinner.
I'll tell you all about it.

17:07.109 --> 17:08.318
Are you serious?

17:08.318 --> 17:09.403
Come on.

