and this is California.

35:52.567 --> 35:55.903
This is what our life is, baby,
grand adventures.

35:55.903 --> 35:57.780
I just want us to take them together.

35:58.531 --> 36:00.616
I do too, but...

36:01.659 --> 36:02.952
You know what?

36:04.370 --> 36:05.204
Come on.

36:06.414 --> 36:08.499
Let's take the biggest adventure of all.

36:13.880 --> 36:15.548
Kam, what are you doing?

36:15.548 --> 36:18.134
What I should have done
that night in Rome.

36:27.393 --> 36:28.978
Marry me, Sasha Snow.

36:30.438 --> 36:34.358
I will give you a life bigger
and better than you ever dreamed.

36:34.358 --> 36:37.862
When I'm through this program,
we can go anywhere you want.

36:37.862 --> 36:41.532
I just-- I don't wanna
wake up a single morning

36:41.532 --> 36:44.660
without you in my arms.

36:52.376 --> 36:53.920
Okay, fine.

36:53.920 --> 36:55.379
Is that a yes?

36:55.379 --> 36:58.049
- Are you gonna be my wife, Sasha Snow?
- Yes!

36:58.049 --> 37:00.218
- Yes?
- Yes, yes.

37:00.218 --> 37:02.386
-  Yes? Oh, my God.
-  Yes.

37:12.605 --> 37:13.981
It's been 17 years,

37:13.981 --> 37:17.401
and I have never stopped
thinking about that moment.

37:18.444 --> 37:21.113
I know things went sideways,
but none of that matters now.

37:21.113 --> 37:22.073
Stop, stop.

37:23.199 --> 37:24.200
This is--

37:25.618 --> 37:26.452
I--

37:28.663 --> 37:29.789
I need a second.

37:31.499 --> 37:34.877
- Sasha, wait.
- No, you wait.

37:36.545 --> 37:37.630
For once.

37:56.607 --> 37:57.441
Sash?

37:59.193 --> 38:00.111
Gran?

38:00.945 --> 38:01.904
Hey.

38:02.822 --> 38:04.115
What are you doing?

38:05.574 --> 38:07.368
More like what are you doing?

38:07.994 --> 38:10.746
Packing to move to Cali
with my hot fiancé.

38:11.289 --> 38:13.874
Just giving it all up for some man?

38:14.458 --> 38:16.502
Gran, it is one semester.

38:16.502 --> 38:19.338
It already was one semester.

38:19.338 --> 38:21.590
Now it's a year, at least.

38:22.425 --> 38:24.552
You are slipping away from yourself.

38:24.552 --> 38:26.387
That's not what this is.

38:26.387 --> 38:28.681
I know guys like Kam.

38:29.473 --> 38:30.725
All too well.

38:30.725 --> 38:34.979
How easy it is
to get swept up into his dreams.

38:34.979 --> 38:38.065
Sooner or later,
you got to stand up for what you want.

38:38.065 --> 38:41.110
- This is what I want.
- It's not all you want.

38:41.110 --> 38:44.196
I will come back to that later. My work--

38:44.196 --> 38:47.533
That's what everybody says
when they make this choice,

38:47.533 --> 38:52.288
but trust me, a lot of women,
just as smart as you, never do.

38:52.288 --> 38:53.581
Well, I'm not you.

38:55.082 --> 38:56.417
I know what I'm doing.

38:58.044 --> 39:00.212
Then why didn't you open the letter?

39:01.547 --> 39:02.673
From Columbia?

39:02.673 --> 39:06.927
The grad program
that actually is your dream?

39:06.927 --> 39:10.097
Maybe because you were too scared.

39:10.097 --> 39:11.724
Thought you might be tempted,

39:11.724 --> 39:15.394
didn't wanna have a Plan B
you might actually want to take.

39:15.394 --> 39:17.104
That is not the reason.

39:17.104 --> 39:18.147
Then open it.

39:18.689 --> 39:19.648
Fine.

39:37.124 --> 39:39.585
I got in. Okay?

39:40.878 --> 39:42.380
But this changes nothing.

39:44.757 --> 39:50.262
And that alone
should be enough to scare you.

40:01.857 --> 40:03.025
Kam?

40:04.026 --> 40:06.237
- Listen.
- I'm sorry.

40:06.946 --> 40:08.322
I know this is a lot.

40:08.322 --> 40:11.367
I don't know what went wrong before.

40:11.367 --> 40:15.579
Clearly, you didn't feel
as much as I did, but--

40:15.579 --> 40:16.831
Bullshit!

40:17.748 --> 40:19.583
That was never the problem.

40:19.583 --> 40:23.629
It wasn't that I didn't feel enough.
It's that I felt too much.

40:24.463 --> 40:25.756
What are you talking about?

40:27.007 --> 40:29.593
You can't just bring me here,
to this place,

40:29.593 --> 40:32.972
and expect me to drop everything again.

40:33.973 --> 40:35.850
- Wait, Sasha, please.
- No.

40:36.392 --> 40:38.144
This is what you do, Kam.

40:38.144 --> 40:40.521
You go from zero to 60 in a second,

40:40.521 --> 40:43.274
and sweep everything along in your path.

40:45.651 --> 40:48.821
But I will not lose myself again.

40:55.536 --> 40:58.038
You didn't have to bring me
all the way back uptown.

40:58.038 --> 41:01.792
I know the cool kids
never cross 14th Street.

41:01.792 --> 41:03.961
Well, I'm not that cool.

41:04.587 --> 41:06.505
Besides, I've had
good luck in these parts.

41:06.505 --> 41:07.423
Oh, yeah?

41:07.423 --> 41:11.010
Well, thank you for an amazing evening,

41:11.677 --> 41:13.137
one I honestly...

41:15.514 --> 41:17.391
I didn't know if I'd ever have again.

41:18.017 --> 41:19.685
This is just the beginning.

41:21.312 --> 41:22.313
Promise.

41:34.283 --> 41:35.326
I'm sorry.

41:38.412 --> 41:40.748
I have to take it slow.

41:40.748 --> 41:43.125
- This is all--
- Don't worry.

41:44.960 --> 41:46.170
We got time.

41:47.379 --> 41:50.674
Plus, I just pictured
the whole thing in my mind,

41:50.674 --> 41:54.386
and it was... incredible.

42:02.019 --> 42:04.396
- I'm gonna go back to work.
- Okay.

42:06.357 --> 42:08.359
- Have a good night.
- Yeah, you too.

42:53.112 --> 42:54.530
Oh, my God.

42:55.239 --> 42:56.991
What happened?

42:59.577 --> 43:00.911
Gran's right.

43:02.621 --> 43:06.542
I can't do this. I can't just throw
everything away for some guy.

43:07.293 --> 43:10.045
- Well, what did Kam say?
- Nothing.

43:11.714 --> 43:12.840
I didn't tell him.

43:13.424 --> 43:14.925
I couldn't. I just...

43:16.719 --> 43:19.305
turned around at the airport
and walked out.

43:20.180 --> 43:21.599
So he doesn't even know?

43:33.527 --> 43:35.070
Sash, answer it.

43:35.696 --> 43:37.823
Tell him what's going on.

43:37.823 --> 43:38.991
I can't.

43:40.951 --> 43:42.911
If I do, I won't stay strong.

43:44.204 --> 43:46.248
I'll be on the next flight out. I know it.

43:50.794 --> 43:51.712
Bills.

44:12.232 --> 44:13.484
Hey, how's it going?

44:14.485 --> 44:17.029
I screwed up big time.

44:17.029 --> 44:18.238
Already?

44:18.238 --> 44:20.324
<i>Mm. Ha.</i>

44:20.324 --> 44:25.954
Um, well, it turns out
that Majid's awesome.

44:26.830 --> 44:29.667
And he's just like me in so many ways.

44:30.876 --> 44:33.212
And what are the odds,
you know, of finding somebody

44:33.212 --> 44:36.256
who's okay with all my baggage,

44:36.256 --> 44:37.591
plus, smoking hot?

44:37.591 --> 44:39.677
So, what did you do?

44:39.677 --> 44:41.053
<i>I chickened out.</i>

44:41.053 --> 44:43.013
At the last second, he was...

44:44.139 --> 44:46.475
trying to kiss me, and--

44:46.475 --> 44:47.768
Oh, girl...

44:49.728 --> 44:52.356
go back and kiss that man.

44:52.356 --> 44:53.982
It is not too late.

44:53.982 --> 44:59.571
Do you know what I was thinking
in that moment when I could smell him

44:59.571 --> 45:03.575
and I could feel his breath on mine?

45:06.328 --> 45:07.579
"How dare you?

45:09.373 --> 45:13.043
What right do you have to be happy?"

45:13.544 --> 45:15.796
<i>Stop. Do not do that.</i>

45:16.338 --> 45:19.466
You're the one who said
we were stepping out of our comfort zones.

45:20.884 --> 45:21.760
You're right.

45:25.639 --> 45:28.767
Okay. All right.

45:29.309 --> 45:31.520
How is it going with Kam?

45:34.481 --> 45:36.233
It's a dream come true.

45:41.822 --> 45:43.866
-  Cooper.
- Dave.

45:43.866 --> 45:45.826
- How are you?
- Burning the midnight oil?

45:45.826 --> 45:48.537
- I'm impressed.
- Well, I'm just checking on Francesca.

45:48.537 --> 45:50.831
We've got the presentation tomorrow.

45:50.831 --> 45:54.042
I can't wait to hear it.
You two are on fire.

45:55.294 --> 45:57.254
- I'll see you tomorrow.
- Betcha.

46:06.180 --> 46:07.139
Hey.

46:10.350 --> 46:11.727
I'm so glad you called.

46:13.437 --> 46:14.521
Stop talking.

46:18.901 --> 46:19.943
Cooper.

46:21.069 --> 46:22.112
What's going on?

46:22.112 --> 46:24.740
<i>♪ Up the whole night ♪</i>

46:26.074 --> 46:29.495
<i>♪ Undefined ♪</i>

46:29.995 --> 46:31.914
I couldn't wait another second.

46:31.914 --> 46:34.708
<i>♪ Can't stop thinking about
Peace and war... ♪</i>

46:34.708 --> 46:36.710
I thought we were being good.

46:42.132 --> 46:43.634
I'm done being good.

46:44.384 --> 46:49.056
<i>♪ The sun takes everything ♪</i>

46:49.056 --> 46:53.101
<i>♪ It could've been anything ♪</i>

46:54.061 --> 46:56.647
<i>♪ I didn't feel anything... ♪</i>

46:56.647 --> 46:58.482
Jesus Christ!

46:58.482 --> 47:00.067
What the hell's going on?

47:02.361 --> 47:04.071
 <i>Love can be scary.</i>

47:05.072 --> 47:06.823
<i>But life can be scary,</i>

47:07.908 --> 47:11.245
<i>and ultimately, a series of risks,</i>

47:13.080 --> 47:14.373
<i>the ones you take,</i>

47:15.749 --> 47:17.000
<i>the ones you don't,</i>

47:18.335 --> 47:20.712
<i>the ones you wish you had.</i>

47:21.880 --> 47:24.841
<i>But perhaps, the biggest risk of all</i>

47:25.551 --> 47:28.387
<i>is allowing yourself to let go.</i>

47:31.348 --> 47:33.684
<i>To break free of the past,</i>

47:33.684 --> 47:35.394
<i>live in the present,</i>

47:36.687 --> 47:37.854
<i>and believe...</i>

47:38.814 --> 47:41.275
<i>you really can make your own tomorrow.</i>

47:41.275 --> 47:45.821
<i>♪ It could've been anything ♪</i>

47:45.821 --> 47:52.411
<i>♪ I didn't feel anything ♪</i>

47:58.125 --> 47:58.959
Majid.

48:00.794 --> 48:03.880
<i>♪ Up the whole night ♪</i>

48:05.716 --> 48:09.261
<i>♪ Underline ♪</i>

48:11.471 --> 48:17.102
<i>♪ Chain smoking like
No, it ain't right... ♪</i>

48:17.102 --> 48:18.353
You came back.

48:20.939 --> 48:22.149
It's that itch.

48:26.695 --> 48:27.863
Hey, man.

48:28.614 --> 48:33.118
<i>♪ It could've been anything ♪</i>

48:33.118 --> 48:35.996
<i>♪ I didn't feel anything... ♪</i>

48:35.996 --> 48:37.164
What are you doing?

48:37.789 --> 48:39.124
Do you guys know each other?

48:39.750 --> 48:41.543
Brad's one of my investors.

48:45.213 --> 48:46.673
Oh, my God.

48:48.300 --> 48:49.343
He's the guy.

48:52.179 --> 48:54.806
Hey, honey. Who's this?
